libmod
    DESCRIPTION
        my playground for developing kernel modules
        
        for more info run
        
            make

    USAGE
        Use ./tag to move through versions & create dev branches

        1. create a fork of this repository & clone into it

        2. check the current tag

            $ ./tag
            > v0.0.10

        3. create a dev-branch
            #
            # Increment one release-minor version
            #
            $ ./tag incr
            > v0.0.11

            # Create and publish a new dev-branch (it will rebase onto the remote branch if it already exists)
            #
            $ ./tag new-dev
            > remote: Create a pull request for 'dev-v0.0.11' on GitHub by visiting:
            > remote:      https://github.com/your-fork/libmod/pull/new/dev-v0.0.11

        4. go to the pull request link & submit it

        5. observer the github actions tests executing

        6. Add commits locally & publish them to your dev-branch

            $ ./tag uc && ./tag p

        Tag traversal funcs

            incr, decr, incm, decm, incM, decM

        Example

            $ ./tag
            > v0.0.10

            $ ./tag incr
            > v0.0.11

            $ ./tag incr
            > v0.0.12

            $ ./tag incm
            > v0.1.12

            $ ./tag decm
            > v0.0.12

            $ ./tag decr
            > v0.0.11

            $ ./tag decr
            > v0.0.10

            $ ./tag incM
            > v1.0.10

            $ ./tag incM
            > v2.0.10

            $ ./tag incm
            > v2.1.10
        
        unstable, under-development, use at your own risk

    - john
